Bowler Metcalf, Sanlam, Tradehold May Move: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-09T22:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/bowler-metcalf-sanlam-tradehold-south-african-stocks-preview.html
  South Africa ’s FTSE/JSE Africa All
Share Index declined for a fourth day, losing 7.05, or less than
0.1 percent, to 31,820.37 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.  Bowler Metcalf Ltd. (BCF SJ): The plastic-packaging maker
said first-half earnings for the period through December
increased 32 percent to 46.2 cents per share, from 34.9 cents a
year earlier. Bowler Metcalf was unchanged at 8.60 rand.    Sanlam Ltd. (SLM)  : South Africa’s second-biggest insurer
publishes earnings for the year ended December. Sanlam declined
35 cents, or 1.3 percent, to 27.50 rand.    Tradehold Ltd. (TDH)  : The retail  investment company  said
it will raise 650 million rand ($94.6 million) in a rights offer
at a rate of 299 new shares for every 100 owned. The rights
offer price will be 6.26 rand a share. Tradehold was unchanged
at 7.50 rand a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
